\section{Briefing}

This is the hard copy of the C++ script written for the questions on Problem Sheet 3. The whole script is used to create 4 functions with a main.cpp file. 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Takes a long as an argument. If the number divides by 3 but not by 2 the function prints “Bingo!” otherwise it prints “Fooey!”
    \item Takes two double arguments, $x$ and $y$, as its arguments. Computes and returns $f(x) = y^2 x^2 + 13 y x^3 - 2x^4$
    \item Takes a string as an argument. Prints the string in reverse.
    \item Takes a string and a long, N, as arguments. The function prints the Nth, 2Nth, 3Nth, ... , characters of the string given.
\end{itemize}



